            <div class="reading-note" data-cid="23194517">
              <div class="short">
                
                  <span class="">In my view, competition for the use of scarce resources must be restrained for social survival, because rent dissipation under unrestrained competition would result in starvation for all. These restraints can assume a variety of forms or different structures of rights, which then define the institutional nature of the economic system.  (Q: why &quot;rent dissipation under unrestrained competition ...</span>
                <p class="pl">
                  <span class="">2012-12-15 22:20</span>
                  
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="all hidden" style="display:none" >
                In my view, competition for the use of scarce resources must be restrained for social survival, because rent dissipation under unrestrained competition would result in starvation for all. These restraints can assume a variety of forms or different structures of rights, which then define the institutional nature of the economic system.  (Q: why &quot;rent dissipation under unrestrained competition would result in starvation for all&quot;?)
